<%# Cerberus override of Blacklight::SearchHeaderComponent's template.

    Upstream rendered: did_you_mean + sort_and_per_page (which carried the
    sort / per-page / view-type controls AND the pagination bar at the top of
    the results column). We've moved those controls down into the facet sidebar
    (catalog/_search_sidebar), so the top of the results column is now just the
    pagination bar — letting the result list rise to sit level with the
    sidebar's "Limit your search".

    Bookmarks is unaffected: it renders catalog/_sort_and_per_page directly
    (not this component), and keeps the controls there since it has no sidebar. %>
<%= render 'did_you_mean' %>
<%= render 'results_pagination_bar' %>
